The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, January 14, 2004 				 Vaiko moves bail plea
																								Chennai, Jan. 13 (PTI): For the first time since his imprisonment about 18 months ago, MDMK chief Vaiko today moved a designated court for bail.																								Vaiko has been in prison since July 11, 2002, for allegedly speaking in favour of the LTTE at a public meeting in Madurai in June that year.																								The bail application will be heard on January 21 by designated judge L. Rajendran, who had been appointed to hear cases under the anti-terror law.																								Vaiko claimed, in his plea, that his speech did not constitute any offence under the Prevention of Terrorism Act.																								Vaiko also said he had not incited violence of any kind and added that his arrest was a violation of his fundamental rights.																								He also said there was no proof that he had tampered with evidence or influenced prosecution witnesses. 
